# --- luminaries --- #

toi:luminaries      a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "luminaries";
                    too:hasTitle        "the luminaries";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "spotlight";
                    too:hasNodeChildren _:luminaries_kids;
	                  too:hasNodeParent   "influences";
                    too:hasNodeSummary
"""
many of the ideas aspoused by these luminaries have been absorbed so completly into 
current thinking that we may take them for granted, and forget that their notions were
once novel.
""".

_:luminaries_kids   a                    rdfs:Container;
                    rdf:_1               _:norman;
                    rdf:_2               _:dawkins;
                    rdf:_3               _:pinker;
                    rdf:_4               _:tufte.

_:norman				    a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "norman";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "norman";
                    too:hasTitle        "[http://www.jnd.org/ donald norman]";
                    too:hasNodeParent   "luminaries";
                    too:hasNodeSummary

"""
early on i read
[[wikipedia:The_Design_of_Everyday_Things|the design of everyday things]]
in which norman describes some aspects good design, and where i learned the word
[[wikipedia:Affordance affordance]].
he also talks about why many products are poorly designed.
in a more recent design
[[youtube:RlQEoJaLQRA|ted talk]]
he underscores the utility of beauty, and importance of factoring emotion into design.
""".

_:dawkins				    a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "dawkins";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "dawkins";
                    too:hasTitle        "[http://richarddawkins.net/ richard dawkins]";
                    too:hasNodeParent   "luminaries";
                    too:hasNodeSummary

"""
[[wikipedia:The_Selfish_Gene|the selfish gene]]
was a seminal book on evolution, from which we get the word
[[wikipedia:Meme|meme]].
it left me with an end-to-end understanding of the rise of life on earth.
dawkins is also an outspoken
[[wikipedia:Atheist|atheist]],
and proponent of
[[wikipedia:Rationalism|rationalism]].
""".

_:pinker				    a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "pinker";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "pinker";
                    too:hasTitle         "[http://stevenpinker.com/biocv stephen pinker]";
                    too:hasNodeParent   "luminaries";
                    too:hasNodeSummary

"""
i started with
[[wikipedia:The_Language_Instinct|the language instinct]]
which posits that humans are born with an innate capacity to develop grammatical language.
here is a fascinating
[http://comment.rsablogs.org.uk/videos/ rsa animate]
[[youtube:3-son3EJTrU|talk]]
he gave on language and behavior.
i'm currently reading
[[wikipedia:The_Better_Angels_of_Our_Nature|the better angels of our nature]]
which, despite its gruesome descriptions of violence present and past, leaves me optimistic about mankind's future.
""".

_:tufte				    	a                   too:treeNode;
                    too:hasName         "tufte";
                    too:hasNodeIcon     "tufte";
                    too:hasTitle         "[http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/ edward tufte]";
                    too:hasNodeParent   "luminaries";
                    too:hasNodeSummary
                    
#[ ]

"""
tufte's
[http://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/courses one day course]
